Sentencas: The solution impregnation technology was used to prepare a novel core-shell structure cathode for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells (IT-SOFCs).
Titulo: Promoted CO2-poisoning resistance of La0.8Sr0.2MnO3-δ-coated Ba0.5Sr0.5Co0.8Fe0.2O3-δ cathode for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The core was composed of porous Ba0.5Sr0.5Co0.8Fe0.2O3-delta (BSCF) backbone with high oxygen conductivity, while the dense shell consisted of La0.8Sr0.2MnO3-delta (LSM) high catalytic activity and the excellent CO2-poisoning resistance.
Titulo: Promoted CO2-poisoning resistance of La0.8Sr0.2MnO3-δ-coated Ba0.5Sr0.5Co0.8Fe0.2O3-δ cathode for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The presence of the dense LSM shell prevented the BSCF cathode from being poisoned by CO2, and improved its electrochemical performance.
Titulo: Promoted CO2-poisoning resistance of La0.8Sr0.2MnO3-δ-coated Ba0.5Sr0.5Co0.8Fe0.2O3-δ cathode for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The best performance was achieved when the BSCF cathode was impregnated twice in the LSM precursor solution and coated by LSM shell.
Titulo: Promoted CO2-poisoning resistance of La0.8Sr0.2MnO3-δ-coated Ba0.5Sr0.5Co0.8Fe0.2O3-δ cathode for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells
